sentences.english: Anomalous refraction is believed to be the main error source for classical astrometry.
sentences.chinese: 反常折射已成爲傳統天體測量學的主要誤差來源。

sentences.english: Industrial class conflict was a symptom of anomie .
sentences.chinese: 工業階級矛盾就是一種反常的症象。

sentences.english: It is well known that accretion disks are hydrodynamic disks with anomalous viscosity.
sentences.chinese: 天體物理吸積盤是具有反常粘滯的流體盤。

sentences.english: This is the most fatal and most illogical social perversion that can possibly be imagined.
sentences.chinese: 這是可能想像的最致命和最不合邏輯社會反常。

sentences.english: The effect of the anomalous magnetic moment of the nucleon on the value of the internal conversion coefficient is investigated.
sentences.chinese: 本文討論核子的反常磁矩對於內轉換系數數值的影響。

sentences.english: Plagueis, the wise, was an adept of some of the most arcane and unnatural applications of the Force.
sentences.chinese: 智者普雷格斯熟諳一些最神祕最反常的原力應用。

sentences.english: "The Internet is the modern-day freak show, " says Szymanski.
sentences.chinese: “網絡就是現代的反常秀，”斯澤曼斯基說。

sentences.english: These unusual instances will be limited to a segment of the demand curve.
sentences.chinese: 這些反常情況僅限於在需求曲線的某一部分上。

sentences.english: The bird is not itself today.
sentences.chinese: 這隻鳥今天有點兒反常。

sentences.english: There are more than 100 types of cancer, characterized by abnormal cell growth.
sentences.chinese: 以反常細胞增殖爲特點的惡性腫瘤有100多種類型。
這是歷史上最大的反常。

sentences.english: Bush's own ideological inclinations against regulation certainly contributed to the financial crisis.
sentences.chinese: 布什自己違反常規的空想傾向無疑造成了金融危機。

sentences.english: Her works are modern and do not follow traditional narrative modes.
sentences.chinese: 她的作品既是現代的又是違反常規敘述模式的。

sentences.english: They report on their findings, including diseases and other abnormalities.
sentences.chinese: 他們要對自己的發現做報告，包括疾病等反常情況。
